@ipax/core
==========

This package contains code derived from third-party sources listed below.
A license has been requested from each author and is pending full terms.

1. IPAX 2 — Santiago Bustelo
   Website : https://www.bustelo.com.ar/
   Source  : https://icograma.com/index.php
   Status  : Permission granted 2026-06-10 — CC-BY attribution terms

   The following files are derived works of IPAX 2 (most recently ported
   from vendor revision r.20260712 — see /vendor/r.20260712 at the repo
   root for the unmodified drop this port was made from):
     src/ipax-core.js          — scoring orchestrator (ported to Node.js ESM)
     src/ipax-color-math.js    — OKLCh color space conversions
     src/ipax-apca-bridge.js   — APCA Lc calculation and font sizing
     src/ipax-ergonomics.js    — perceptual penalty and reward engine
     src/ipax-dictionary.js    — penalty/reward data and scientific references

   Adaptation: IIFE browser modules converted to ES module exports.
   `graphical` mode (non-text WCAG 1.4.11 floor, edge-aware ergonomics
   weighting) is an original extension not present in the vendor source.
   The scoring algorithms, physiological models, and penalty/reward data
   are reproduced with the intent to credit and obtain permission.

2. APCA W3 — Andrew Somers / Myndex Research
   Repository : https://github.com/Myndex/apca-w3
